str.replace(',', '').str.replace('$', '').str.strip(')').str.replace('(', '-').astype(float)

In [15]:
col2agg = {
 'Net Item Revenue (Fulfilled)':'sum',
 'Net Items (Fulfilled)':'sum',
 'Gross Orders (Fulfilled)':'sum',
 'Net Sell Through Items (Week)':'mean',
 'MSRP of Sold Items':'sum',
 'Avg. Item Age When Sold':'mean',
 'Avg. Item Age EOW':'mean',
 'EOW Inventory For Sale $':'sum',
 'EOW Inventory For Sale Items':'sum',
 'MSRP of EOW Inventory':'sum'
}
In [16]:
for col, agg_method in col2agg.items():
    ax=hb_sales.groupby('Sales Week')[col].agg(agg_method).plot(label=col, color='Blue')
    plt.title(col,fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel(col,fontsize=14)
    plt.xlabel('Sales Week',fontsize=14)
    plt.grid(True)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.WeekdayLocator(byweekday=mdates.SU))
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%d %b %Y'))
    plt.xticks(fontsize=14,rotation=90)
    plt.yticks(fontsize=14)
    plt.show()

Conclusion: we have highest revenue in Dec. Then it is gradually trending down. This might be caused by seasonality. We can further breakdown the reveune in departments to understand each department's performance. Moreover, the time for items to be sold has been increased drastically.

EOW_discount=EOW_discount.\
groupby(['Sales Week','Department']).\
agg({'EOW Inventory For Sale $':'sum',\
     'MSRP of EOW Inventory':'sum',\
     'Net Items (Fulfilled)' :'mean',\
    'Net Item Revenue (Fulfilled)':'sum'}).reset_index()

EOW_discount['rough_discount_rate']=1-(EOW_discount['MSRP of EOW Inventory']-\

Positive Correlation
Kids Storage, Kitchen and Dining,Outdoor Storage are positively correlated with discount rate, with higher discount rate, more items can be sold.
Negative Correlation
Furniture, Kids Furniture are negatively correlated with discount rate, with higher discount rate, less items can be sold, or the vice versa.
No Correlation
The sold number of items on Outdoor Furniture and Storage is not correlated with discount rate.

Conclusion and Suggestions:

  1. We have a peak sales at the week of 2018-12-02, which is followed by a return spike at the week of 2018-12-30. Returned products are mainly from kitchen and dinning department, which accounts for about 1% of the revenue at the week of 2018-12-02.

  2. Kitchen and Dinning was the main driver in revenue. Particuarly for spoons and forks, the sell through rates are the highest among all departments. Spoons has highest revenues and no orders are returned. From the last 15 weeks, there is no returned orders for spoons. Moreover, the revenue on Kids Furniture, Kids Storage, Outdoor Furniture and Outdoor Storage are highly correlated and at similar magnitude. It might be beneficial to plan the inventory of these department at similar level.

  3. Overall, the times on selling products are increasing for all departments, further analysis is needed to understand the reason, it might be caused by some common factors.

  4. Kids Storage, Kitchen and Dining,Outdoor Storage are positively correlated with discount rate, with higher discount rate, more items can be sold.Furniture, Kids Furniture are negatively correlated with discount rate, with higher discount rate, less items can be sold, or the vice versa. The sold number of items on Outdoor Furniture and Storage is not correlated with discount rate.
